The paper deals with online routing over dynamic networks, which involves modeling and estimation of time-varying link costs. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also formulates the problem as a combinatorial bandit optimization problem, which is a common topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper considers scenarios where routing decisions are made at different points in the network, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SY, and cs.AI, in that order.
